    <title type="text">Open Access Journal: Porphyra: la prima rivista online sul mondo di
      Bisanzio</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<span style="font-size: xx-small;">&nbsp;First posted in AWOL 22
      September 2011. Updated 30 July 2013]</span><br /><br /><a
      href="http://www.porphyra.it/">Porphyra: la prima rivista online sul mondo di
      Bisanzio</a><br />ISSN: 2240-5240<br /><blockquote><img
      alt="http://www.porphyra.it/wp-content/themes/Ad-Clerum-2/Ad-Clerum-2/images/creation.jpg"
      class="decoded" height="75"
      src="http://www.porphyra.it/wp-content/themes/Ad-Clerum-2/Ad-Clerum-2/images/creation.jpg"
      width="320" /></blockquote><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><b>WHAT IS PORPHYRA</b></span><br
      /><span style="font-size: x-small;">Porphyra is the first Italian on-line magazine to
      focus exclusively on Byzantium.</span><br /><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Founded in 2003 by Nicola Bergamo, it is currently one of tha many ways through
      which the</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">Associazione
      Culturale Bisanzio fosters and promotes Byzantine history, culture and
      civilization.</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">From March 2006
      until December 2011 it has been directed by Matteo Broggini.</span><br /><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">From January 2012 to present the director is Nicola
      Bergamo.</span> </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><b>THE AIMS OF
      PORPHYRA&nbsp;</b></span><br /><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Porphyra publishes and divulges articles and essays of high scientific value,
      always approved by</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">a committe
      of the most esteemed academic members worldwide. Master degree or PhD are
      the</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">criteria required to
      publish, along with thorough research, passion and method.</span><br /><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Our aim is to contribute to the transimission of an accurate
      knowledge and perception of what</span><br /><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Byzantine culture was, and of its connections with both, our past and our present.
      We also aim at</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">fostering the
      awareness of how much our culture has inherited from the Eastern Roman
      Empire.</span></blockquote><blockquote><div style="text-align:
      left;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><b><a
